You have 2 related issues in your cluster:


---

🔴 Problem Summary

1. ❌ network operator degraded

failed to validate trust bundle for proxy trustedCA 'harbor-ca':
ConfigMap "harbor-ca" is missing "ca-bundle.crt"

2. ❌ machine-config operator degraded

ca-bundle.crt not found in openshift-config/harbor-ca

👉 Both errors clearly say:

> Your ConfigMap exists, but the key name is wrong




---

🔍 Root Cause

Your current ConfigMap:

data:
  sribharbor.sec.samsung.net: "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE----- ..."

❌ This is WRONG for OpenShift proxy trusted CA

👉 OpenShift expects EXACT key name:

ca-bundle.crt


---

✅ Fix (VERY IMPORTANT)

You must recreate or update the ConfigMap with correct key.


---

🔧 Option 1: Quick Fix (Recommended)

Run this:

oc create configmap harbor-ca \
  -n openshift-config \
  --from-file=ca-bundle.crt=/path/to/your/cert.crt \
  --dry-run=client -o yaml | oc apply -f -

👉 Replace /path/to/your/cert.crt with your actual cert file


---

🔧 Option 2: Manual Fix

Edit ConfigMap:

oc edit cm harbor-ca -n openshift-config

Change this:

data:
  sribharbor.sec.samsung.net: "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----"

👉 TO:

data:
  ca-bundle.crt: |
    -----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
    MIIFzTCCA7WgAwIBAgIUJkMdghBJnGoJ39xviWGyz2e+RjYwDQYJKoZIhvcNAQEN
    ...
    -----END CERTIFICATE-----

⚠️ Important:

Remove \r\n

Proper multiline format

Key must be exactly ca-bundle.crt



---

🔄 After Fix

Wait 2–5 minutes, then check:

oc get co


